 paper/the readme.\r\nOn the other hand, the reconstruction loss is quite high (approx. 0.5) while the KL loss is approx. zero, and the VAE fails to reconstruct accurately molecules.\r\nThis looks like posterior collapse to me (indeed, all smiles are encoded into roughly the same mean/variances), and while this still yields a nice generator, it removes the main interest of the VAE (obtaining a meaningful latent space) in contrast to a plain charRNN for instance.\r\nAny thoughts/advices/comments on the matter?\r\n\r\nThanks","closed_by":{"login":"danpol","id":1181277,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExODEyNzc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1181277?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol","html_url":"https://github.com/danpol","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danpol/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/molecularsets/moses/issues/45/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/molecularsets/moses/issues/45/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}